al thought most famously associated with Ronald Dworkin, Hershovitz engages with important legal and political controversies of our time, including recent debates about constitutional interpretation and the obligations of citizens and officials to obey the law.Leavened by entertaining personal stories, guided by curiosity rather than ideology, moving beyond entrenched dichotomies like the opposition between positivism and natural law, Law Is a Moral Practice is a thought-provoking investigation of the philosophical issues behind real-world legal debates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLaw and ethics. 0aLawxInterpretation and construction. 0aLawxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aLaw-Interpretation and construction. 0aLaw-Moral and ethical aspects. 7aLAW / Jurisprudence.2bisacsh  aCongress.  aHLA Hart.  aJoseph Raz.  aMark Greenberg.  aSupreme Court.  aauthority.  acommunity.  aduties.  aenforcement.  afairness.  alitigation.  anorms.  aownership.  apromises.  aproperty.  arealism.  aresponsibilities.  arights.  arule.  atextualism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074970040uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674294875?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674294875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674294875/original  a978-3-11-074970-0  Harvard University Press Co